{"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Wrapped","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Wrapped"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot7WrappedC","title":"Wrapped","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Wrapped","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritedBy","title":"Inherited By","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Object"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Wrapped"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Wrapped implements Equatable based on an identity based on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pointer to the Godot native object and also implements the Identifiable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"protocol using this pointer."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Wrapped subclasses come in two forms: straight bindings to the Godot","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API which are used to expose capabilities to developers.   These objects, referred"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to as Framework types do not have any additional state associated in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift, so they can be discarded or recreated as many times as it is needed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When user subclass Wrapped, they might have state associated with them,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so those objects are preserved and are not thrown away until they are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"explicitly relinquished by both Godot and any references you might hold to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"them.   These are known as User types."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any subclass ends up calling the Wrapped(StringName) constructor which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provides the name of the most-derived framework type, and this constructor"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"determines whether this is a Framework type or a user type.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To register User types with the framework make sure you call the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"register<T:Wrapped> (type: T.Type)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" method like this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"register (type: MySpinningCube.self)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you do not call this method, many of the overloads that Godot would","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"call you back on will not be invoked.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/wrapped"]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Operators","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Wrapped\/==(_:_:)"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Wrapped\/init()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Wrapped\/init(nativeHandle:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","identi